cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the automatic detection of polyps in colonoscopy images and videos using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses transfer learning, image augmentation, and post-learning methods, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The use of videos in the experiments suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) could also be a relevant category. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
